The world's most institutionally dominant people — not through raw power but through
relentless institution-building. From the Keeper civilization's road networks to the
Solar Court's Great Pyramid to the cities of Midgaard and Kowloon, human history is a
record of organizations that amplify both achievement and failure. The Ashfall Era's
Spirebound Conclave, the Black Ledger, and the sealed warrant records are equally human
constructions. Most of what shapes this world, for good and ill, traces back to a human
decision made inside a human institution.
